    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hollow, often decorative forms, where mixtures are placed and left to sit, in order for them to retain the shapes of the decorative forms.   Hollow forms or matrices, often in decorative shapes into which food mixture is left to set to assume the shape of the mold.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
